description:
Data acquired from 2017-09-30 until 2017-11-29
DSO Color Mapping: Stars RGB, Nebulae Modified Hubble Palette
Original Image Scale: 0.97
Note: This scope is located at Sierra Remote Observatory. I personally configured and installed this scope and make regular trips to SRO to perform maintenance and upgrades. When not on site, I operate the scope nightly from home using a remote desktop application.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This is the lower back region of the famous Soul Nebula. The principle emission nebulae in the frame are LBN 667 and LBN 670. Considering all of the fascinating features of The Soul, this area only brings up the rear in terms of popularity.
title: Seat of the Soul - IC 1848 The Soul Nebula
